The paper deals with revenue maximization in auctions, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The use of a modified version of the core decomposition lemma suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper proposes a mechanism for selling items based on the buyer's valuation, which involves decision-making and optimization, making it relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of approximation algorithms to achieve a constant fraction of the optimal revenue suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with auctions and revenue maximization, which are topics in economic theory, making it relevant to the category of electronic commerce (cs.EC).
